---
name: scljet-sql-where-bool
description: SclJet SQL compound WHERE — AND / OR with correct precedence (AND binds tighter than OR), matches reference sqlite3
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet SQL compound WHERE (AND / OR)

`WHERE` accepts a chain of comparisons joined by `AND` / `OR`. As in SQL, `AND` binds tighter than
`OR`, so `a AND b OR c AND d` means `(a AND b) OR (c AND d)`. A row is kept when any OR-group holds
and, within a group, every AND condition holds. Every result is byte-identical to reference sqlite3
running the same SQL on the same file (verified out-of-band); locked here across backends.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[queryImage, renderRows](std/scljet/sql.ssc)

```scalascript
def show(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): Unit =
  queryImage(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) => println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
    case Right(rows) => println(sql + " => " + renderRows(rows).toString)

buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "emp", "CREATE TABLE emp(id INTEGER, name TEXT, dept INTEGER, salary INTEGER)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText("ann"), SqlInteger(10L), SqlInteger(100L)),
       List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlText("bob"), SqlInteger(20L), SqlInteger(250L)),
       List(SqlInteger(3L), SqlText("cat"), SqlInteger(10L), SqlInteger(300L)),
       List(SqlInteger(4L), SqlText("dan"), SqlInteger(30L), SqlInteger(150L)),
       List(SqlInteger(5L), SqlText("eve"), SqlInteger(20L), SqlInteger(250L)),
       List(SqlInteger(6L), SqlText("flo"), SqlInteger(10L), SqlInteger(120L)))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db) =>
    show(db, "SELECT id, name FROM emp WHERE dept = 10 AND salary > 100")
    show(db, "SELECT id FROM emp WHERE dept = 10 OR dept = 30")
    show(db, "SELECT id, dept, salary FROM emp WHERE dept = 10 AND salary >= 120 OR dept = 30")
    show(db, "SELECT name FROM emp WHERE salary >= 120 AND salary <= 250 ORDER BY id")
    show(db, "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM emp WHERE dept = 10 AND salary > 100")
    show(db, "SELECT id FROM emp WHERE dept = 20 AND name = 'bob' OR dept = 30 AND salary = 150")
```
